# Inverse Half-Grid Design Audit

Accepted outcome: `inverse_near_miss_only`
Headline classification: `late_q_direct_operand_after_root_subtract_near_miss`

## Test Design

This audit starts from the desired readout grid instead of from candidate formulas.
The only promoted target is pointwise half-ULP separation from the clean arm: `phase delta == 0.5 mod 1`.
Measured route families from the late-q and early-operand campaigns are regrouped into design principles and ranked by target conformity.

## Required Findings

1. Natural half-grid design principle supported: `False`.
2. Natural support candidate: `False`.
3. Natural near miss found: `True`.
4. Best natural principle: `late_q_direct_operand_after_root_subtract` classified `half_grid_near_miss`.
   Best fixture/mask/fraction: `schwarzschild` / `f_binade_-1` / `0.7272727272727273`.
5. Synthetic detector conforms by construction: `True`.
6. Early operand principles are same-phase anti-conformers: `True`.
7. Double precision language justified: `False`.

